COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 172300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A RIDGE EXTENDS NE FM THE AZORES HIGH
TOWARDS THE UK. AT THE SAME TIME A LOW 990 IS LOCATED
TO THE SW OF ICELAND SLOW MOV. DURING TUESDAY THE RIDGE
DECLINING AS A FRONTAL TROUGH PUSHES E INTO THE UK ON
WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY PERHAPS WITH A NEW DEVELOPING LOW
MOV QCKY N OVER ROCKALL AND BAILEY TO FORM A MAIN LOW
CENTRE JUST S OF ICELAND ON THURSDAY AROUND 990. HIGH
PRESSURE IS EXP TO PERSIST ACROSS MUCH OF SCANDINAVIA
THROUGH THE PERIOD. STRG WINDS ARE EXP TO AFFECT FAIR
ISLE FOR MUCH OF THE PERIOD AND ARE LIKELY TO ALSO EXTEND
INTO VIKING AND N UTSIRE ON WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY AND
PERHAPS CROMARTY FOR A TIME. ELSEWHERE WINDS LOOK LIKE
REMAINING PREDOMINANTLY NON-HAZARDOUS THROUGH THE PERIOD
